de.lmu.ifi.dbs.elki.database.ids.integer

Class IntegerDBIDArrayQuickSort

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.lmu.ifi.dbs.elki.database.ids.integer.IntegerDBIDArrayQuickSort

  • @Reference(authors="Vladimir Yaroslavskiy",
           title="Dual-Pivot Quicksort",
           booktitle="http://iaroslavski.narod.ru/quicksort/",
           url="http://iaroslavski.narod.ru/quicksort/")
 class IntegerDBIDArrayQuickSort
extends Object
    Class to sort an integer DBID array, using a modified quicksort. Two array iterators will be used to seek to the elements to compare, while the backing storage is a plain integer array. The implementation is closely based on:

    Dual-Pivot Quicksort
    Vladimir Yaroslavskiy

    Since:
    0.5.5
    Author:
    Erich Schubert
